    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "613f4292ddf3b4ed",
      "text": "Hetzner Online \tFrom Hetzner's rescue image one can boot into the nixos installer using a custom kexec image that is configured with the IPv6 provided by Hetzner and also contain your ssh key.\n\nTip: The kexec tarball as generated by nixos-generators can remain put into the /boot partition for future use. Hetzner also provides an interface to upload your own ISO-images. Also here you may want to build your own iso-image, which has openssh with ssh keys due the lack of a remote console. An easier method to install NixOS on Hetzner, is to use the existing integration into NixOps. Also see Install NixOS on Hetzner Online for future information "
